Class Node<IN,OUT>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.robopupu.api.graph.Node<IN,OUT>
  • Type Parameters:
    IN - The input type.
    OUT - The output type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    InputNode<IN>, OutputNode<OUT>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Action1Node, ActionNode, BooleanNode, BufferNode, ByteNode, CharacterNode, ConcatNode, ConcatStringsNode, ConditionNode, CountNode, DistinctNode, DoubleNode, FilterNode, FirstNode, FloatNode, FunctionNode, IntegerNode, LastNode, ListNode, LongNode, MergeNode, NthNode, ObserverNode, OutputActionNode, RepeatNode, RequestNode, ReverseNode, ShortNode, SimpleNode, SkipNode, SkipWhileNode, StringNode, SumNode, TakeNode, TextViewNode, ThreadNode, TimerNode, TriggerNode, ViewNode, ZipInputNode, ZipNode

    public class Node<IN,OUT>
extends java.lang.Object
implements InputNode<IN>, OutputNode<OUT>
    Node is a base class for all nodes.
